> ### 💡 The Sifting Edge: Dynamic Shaker Screen Screening
> 
> 
> High-speed dicing inherently creates a massive volume of loose crumbs and micro-fragments. Elite manufacturers pass all diced cubes over a sequence of vibratory sifting screens before they enter the seasoning and baking phase. This dynamic mechanical separation ensures that loose bread dust is entirely cleared out of the product stream. If left unchecked, these loose crumbs will absorb your expensive topical oils and spices, leaving you with patchy, unevenly seasoned croutons and a bag filled with heavy debris at the bottom.

